'''Where can you study P2P-related subjects?'''


Here is a [http://chimprawk.blogspot.com/2006/09/designing-social-software-syllabus.html provisional list of courses related to social technology]

Trebor Scholz monitors [http://del.icio.us/trebor/media_study_courses Media Study courses]; F. Stutzman also monitors [http://del.icio.us/fstutzman/syllabi syllabi on communication and technology courses]

The P2P Foundation recommends:

* [[Design for Cultural and Urban Commons]]: post-graduate M.A. course in London [http://www.londonmet.ac.uk/courses/postgraduate/design-for-cultural-commons---ma/]

* [[Digital Citizens Basics]], an online course on digital rights and duties, proposed by Marco Fioretti, affordable to all for 7 Euro [http://mfioretti.com/online-course-digital-citizens-basics] 


